sec.p:
This type of reaction could also be used for synthesis of such acyclic nucleoside analogues as:
glycerol-derived acyclonucleoside [Base + H2N–CH2–CH2(OH)–CH2(OH)], this compound phosphorylated at one or both hydroxyl positions could make a backbone with phosphate bonds;
acrolein-derived nucleoside analogues [Base + HOCH2CH(CH2NH2)CH2OH];
common nucleosides [Base + ribosylamine] (it is an one step process of glicoside bond forming with good yields and great similarity with the processes of the de-novo pyrimidine nucleosides biosynthesis).

First, Gly2 is produced by the chemical bond formation between two Gly molecules. The number of produced Gly2 molecules is shown as
